Sentencas: Characteristics of stainless steel grade AISI 441 deposited with Mn, Co and 10 wt% La-0.6-Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC) powder mixtures as cathode contact materials in solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) stacks are studied.
Titulo: High temperature (800 °C) oxidation of AISI 441 stainless steel with Mn-Co contact layers for SOFC stacks

Sentencas: Microstructures of both uncoated and coated steel are examined after ageing at 800 degrees C for 10,000 h in air.
Titulo: High temperature (800 °C) oxidation of AISI 441 stainless steel with Mn-Co contact layers for SOFC stacks

Sentencas: It is found that the free surfaces of both uncoated and Mn -Co coated (Mn/Co ratio = 1:2 and 2:1) steel coupons suffer severe oxide scale spallation.
Titulo: High temperature (800 °C) oxidation of AISI 441 stainless steel with Mn-Co contact layers for SOFC stacks

Sentencas: In contrast, on the contact surfaces of uncoated coupons Mn-Cr-Fe spinels develop; and Mn -Co spinels grow on Mn-Co and Mn-Co-LSC coated (Mn/Co ratio = 1:1) coupons.
Titulo: High temperature (800 °C) oxidation of AISI 441 stainless steel with Mn-Co contact layers for SOFC stacks

Sentencas: Precipitates of Ti, Si and Nb oxides segregate at the steel/scale interface, weakening scale adherence.
Titulo: High temperature (800 °C) oxidation of AISI 441 stainless steel with Mn-Co contact layers for SOFC stacks

Sentencas: Area specific resistance (ASR) of steel/powder/La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) assemblies is measured at 800 degrees C for 5043 h in air.
Titulo: High temperature (800 °C) oxidation of AISI 441 stainless steel with Mn-Co contact layers for SOFC stacks

Sentencas: The Mn-Co-LSC mixtures (Mn/Co ratio = 1:1 and 1:2) display close ASR values of 21-24 m Omega cm(2), less than the value of 71 m Omega cm(2) from the Mn-Co mixture (Mn/Co ratio = 2:1).
Titulo: High temperature (800 °C) oxidation of AISI 441 stainless steel with Mn-Co contact layers for SOFC stacks

Sentencas: This is attributed to the lower intrinsic resistivity of the derived Mn-Co oxides as well as good contact with steel and the LSCF wafer.
Titulo: High temperature (800 °C) oxidation of AISI 441 stainless steel with Mn-Co contact layers for SOFC stacks
